      "message": "Interesting, I didn\u0027t notice this. I don\u0027t think it\u0027s a good idea to use a simple std::unique_ptr\u003c\u003e here because Win32 handle values are notoriously difficult to work with and check correctly for correctness. See [1] for an example.\n\nFor example, whether 0 is an acceptable handle value seems to depend on the context / the Win32 API being called.\n\nChromium use a rather complex class to implement that [2], should we do the same if we provide something like that as a generic facility (as opposed to being used only in one source file)\n\n[1] https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/oldnewthing/20040302-00/?p\u003d40443/\n\n[2] https://code.google.com/p/chromium/codesearch#chromium/src/base/win/scoped_handle.h",
